MoneyPrinterTurbo
is an open-source tool that turns a single topic or keyword into a fully ed=
ited short video, no timeline, no manual cuts, no subscriptions.
The problem it solves is real. Making a short video normally means juggling=
 five separate tools: one for scripting, one for voiceover, one for subtitl=
es, one for stock footage, one for editing. This project collapses all of t=
hat into one self-hosted pipeline.
Here is what it handles automatically:
Script generation
using your LLM of choice (GPT, DeepSeek, Gemini, Ollama)
AI voiceover via Edge TTS, free by default
Stock footage pulled from Pexels or Pixabay, royalty-free
Subtitles with custom font, color, and position
Background music, then a rendered HD video ready to post
You can run it via
Web UI, Docker, or CLI
. The repo has over 62K stars on GitHub. The code is free. A 60-second scri=
pt costs under $0.001 with GPT-4o-mini, Edge TTS is free, and Pexels is fre=
e at normal volumes.
