Someone just asked
Claude Fable 5
to build Minecraft. In a browser. From scratch. And it delivered.
The result runs entirely in HTML using Three.js, a 3D graphics library for =
the browser. No assets, no images, no pre-made sounds. Everything is genera=
ted on the fly, including the background music.
Here is what got built in
one shot for ~$30
:
Infinite terrain with biomes: plains, forests, deserts, snowy tundra, ocean=
s
Caves, ore veins, day/night cycle, dynamic lighting, and torches
TNT with chain reactions, block physics, and a full inventory system
Procedurally synthesized audio, including a generative ambient music system
The code is public on GitHub. You can clone it and run it locally with
npm start
, no build step needed.
What this shows: Fable 5 can hold an entire complex codebase in its head an=
d ship it coherently. That opens up rapid prototyping of games, simulations=
, and interactive tools from a single prompt.
