Leaked Anthropic system prompt reveals Claude Fable 5 and new Mythos model =
tier
4,492 Likes
Someone just leaked the internal system prompt for
Claude Fable 5
, Anthropic's newest model, and it reveals a lot about how the product actu=
ally works under the hood.
Here's what's actually interesting for you:
New model tier called Mythos-class
sits above Opus. Fable 5 and Mythos 5 share the same base model, but Mythos=
 drops safety restrictions for approved orgs only.
Artifacts now have persistent storage
across sessions using a key-value API. You can build journals, leaderboards=
, and trackers that actually remember data between chats.
Claude Code, Claude Cowork, and browser/Excel/PowerPoint agents
are all listed as real products you can use today.
The model can switch mid-conversation, so previous messages from a differen=
t model version are still valid.
The storage API is the most useful thing here. You can now build stateful m=
ini-apps inside Claude artifacts without any backend. That opens up real li=
ghtweight tooling without spinning up a server.
